{{anthropology-stub}}
[[Category:Cultural anthropology]]

The abbreviation '''OOAK''' stands for the expression, "'''one of a kind'''."<ref>{{Citation |title=Yachting's 11th one of a kind |journal=Yachting |last= |first= |authorlink= |last2= |first2= |editorn-last= |editorn-first= |edition= |volume=147 |issue=1 |year=1980 |origyear= |page=84 |pages= |publisher=Ziff-Davis |place=New York |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eYP3CgbW5JgC&pg=PA85&lpg=PA85&dq=ooak&source=bl&ots=uIRc-f7xYN&sig=9LSsyHWI4L0j3zbZMKDysAU8RD0&hl=en&sa=X&ei=FuZ3UNfsCLDXigKpz4CQBQ&ved=0CEIQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=ooak&f=false |accessdate= |isbn= |oclc= }}</ref> The term originates in [[yachting]] in 1949 to describe a [[regatta]] race in which ship builders were allowed to enter as many different models of yachts into the regatta as they manufactured, but no more than one of each model (hence, "one of a kind").<ref>{{Citation |title=Yachting's one-of-a-kind regatta |journal=Yachting |last=Trimble |first=Nancy |authorlink= |last2= |first2= |editorn-last= |editorn-first= |edition= |volume=158 |issue=5 |year=1985 |origyear= |page=73 |pages= |publisher=Ziff-Davis |place=New York |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BLg5v41rbmEC&pg=PA73&lpg=PA73&dq=ooak&source=bl&ots=JFtPnypPUB&sig=u7M7Qr-IfMYX7TlwJf5Eb8B3Stk&hl=en&sa=X&ei=FuZ3UNfsCLDXigKpz4CQBQ&ved=0CD4Q6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=ooak&f=false |accessdate= |isbn= |oclc= }}</ref>
Since then the term has found different and expanded use as an Internet acronym, especially with regard to the sale of handmade merchandise which is "one of a kind" with respect to actual production rather than to allowed number of entries in a competition. The term has widespread use in the [[cottage industry]] of [[doll]] making,<ref>{{Citation |title=A date with BJD destiny |last=White-Francis |first=Linda |authorlink= |last2= |first2= |editorn-last= |editorn-first= |edition= |volume=28 |issue=7 |year=2009 |origyear= |page=21 |pages= |publisher=Jones |place=Iola, WI |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kKY9bQQVZQcC&pg=PA21&lpg=PA21&dq=ooak&source=bl&ots=lsPzSjPf1B&sig=uq8_7g3ybue09SSWVyNuGvqvXUc&hl=en&sa=X&ei=dBR3UJjCCaj9iwKCgoGgAQ&ved=0CH4Q6AEwDg#v=onepage&q=ooak&f=false |accessdate= |isbn= |oclc= }}</ref> but is used in any manufacturing sector in which the one-of-a-kind nature of a product signifies its value/importance.
==See also== * [[Art doll]]
